snippet.textDisplay: So, we claimed a big, big win in Arteta's maiden European game in charge. I thought we created chances in the first half but didn't take them with Laca the main culprit. They started better but we grew into the game and went to half time on level terms. We did better in the second half but just as hope was fading away, Laca popped up with what could be a crucial goal thanks to yet another assist from the brilliant Saka. I thought Leno was really solid. He made some good saves to keep us in the game. Sokratis was decent. I don't understand why AMN didn't start ahead of him. Luiz was good. Mustafi was superb yet again. He has been playing really well of late and I really hope he continues like this cos we all know how Mustafi is like. He can play well for some games then make mistakes. Saka was our MOTM by a country mile. He was excellent defensively and really good going forward. This kid really is a talent and we need to tie him down real quick. Xhaka and Guendouzi were poor on the night. You can see just how badly Xhaka plays when he is pressed. Guendouzi kept on falling over which was really pissing me off. He needs to fix up. Willock showed exactly why he isn't good enough. He was ineffective throughout the game and didn't do anything of note. He is simply not good enough to play in the first team. Martinelli started brightly but faded. He really struggled on that right hand side. Auba was pretty anonymous but he was involved in the goal as he held it up well and fed Saka who in turn fed Laca. He needs to be playing up top cos he is useless on the wing. Laca was dreadful for a majority of the game but scored the crucial away goal. He missed a sitter in the first half but you could say he made up for it with the winning goal. I am really happy that he is starting to rediscover his scoring touch and long may it continue. Ceballos was all right when he came on. Pepe didn't have much time to do anything really. I was a bit surprised with Arteta's team selection but in the end we got the job done so I can't really complain. It's now 2 clean sheets in a row and more importantly 2 wins in a row so I hope we get another win in our crucial game against Everton at the weekend. Up the Arsenal. COYG!!
